			<outline text="December 28" created="Fri, 28 Dec 2007 05:00:01 GMT">
				<outline text="Recommendation for Flickr" created="Sat, 29 Dec 2007 04:38:47 GMT">
					<outline text="I've been emailing today with photographers who use Flickr to manage their sets and collections. They like it that people can view their pictures publicly, but they want to control how they're used. RSS, used as a way to distribute pictures, is a new idea for many of them. " created="Sat, 29 Dec 2007 04:38:52 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Based on these conversations I think it's important that they have a way to:" created="Sat, 29 Dec 2007 04:43:13 GMT"/>
					<outline text="1. Turn off the RSS feed for their pictures." created="Sat, 29 Dec 2007 04:40:33 GMT"/>
					<outline text="2. To have their pictures not included in RSS feeds based on tags and searches." created="Sat, 29 Dec 2007 04:40:42 GMT"/>
					<outline text="3. To include their pictures in RSS feeds, but only links to them, and the titles and descriptions, but not as enclosures." created="Sat, 29 Dec 2007 04:40:59 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Of course this recommendation isn't just for Flickr, it's a good idea for any photo-sharing site." created="Sat, 29 Dec 2007 04:41:53 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="FlickrFan, day 2">
					<outline text="Good morning, lots of discussion on many weblogs about the new product, &lt;a href=&quot;http://flickrfan.org/&quot;&gt;FlickrFan&lt;/a&gt;, announced &lt;a href=&quot;http://scripting.com/flickrFan/sn122707.html&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt; last night." created="Fri, 28 Dec 2007 17:18:48 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I'm going to write about it here, a lot, over the coming weeks and months, but first I wanted to link to some of the comments about it." created="Fri, 28 Dec 2007 17:24:10 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Michael Markman: &lt;a href=&quot;http://mickeleh.blogspot.com/2007/12/how-to-use-flickrfan-with-appletv.html&quot;&gt;How to Use FlickrFan with AppleTV&lt;/a&gt;." created="Fri, 28 Dec 2007 22:32:09 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Don Park: &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.docuverse.com/blog/donpark/2007/12/28/daves-new-thingy&quot;&gt;Dave's New Thingy&lt;/a&gt;." created="Fri, 28 Dec 2007 17:24:52 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Rex Hammock: &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.rexblog.com/2007/12/27/17414/&quot;&gt;Dave's cool new thing&lt;/a&gt;." created="Fri, 28 Dec 2007 17:25:53 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I guess it's a &quot;thing&quot; eh? &quot;;-&gt;&quot;" created="Fri, 28 Dec 2007 17:33:11 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Phil Jones: &lt;a href=&quot;http://platformwars.blogspot.com/2007/12/yep-daves-done-it-again.html&quot;&gt;Platform Wars&lt;/a&gt;." created="Fri, 28 Dec 2007 17:59:54 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Michael Gartenberg: &lt;a href=&quot;http://weblogs.jupiterresearch.com/analysts/gartenberg/archives/2007/12/changing_analog.html&quot;&gt;FlickrFan first thoughts&lt;/a&gt;." created="Fri, 28 Dec 2007 18:29:17 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Scoble (yesterday): &lt;a href=&quot;http://scobleizer.com/2007/12/27/the-macmini-hdtv-revolution/&quot;&gt;The MacMini HDTV revolution&lt;/a&gt;." created="Fri, 28 Dec 2007 18:30:36 GMT"/>
					<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://avc.blogs.com/a_vc/2007/12/flickrfan.html&quot;&gt;Fred Wilson&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;http://bijansabet.com/post/22554253&quot;&gt;Bijan Sabet&lt;/a&gt; have been using the software for the last month or so in a variety of forms. " created="Fri, 28 Dec 2007 17:26:39 GMT"/>
					<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.1938media.com/screensaver-20/&quot;&gt;Loren Feldman&lt;/a&gt; marks the moment in history. &quot;;-&gt;&quot;" created="Fri, 28 Dec 2007 22:15:42 GMT"/>
					<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://gigaom.com/2007/12/27/introducing-flickrfan/&quot;&gt;Om Malik came&lt;/a&gt; for a visit last month, we took a walk in the hills, and of course I talked about FlickrFan and did a demo." created="Fri, 28 Dec 2007 17:27:24 GMT"/>
					<outline text="There were other articles and reviews, you can find them on TechMeme or Technorati. One thing I've learned is that takes a bit of time to find the right mix of personal pics from Flickr and news pics from AP. It's an unusual app because whole families can use it, and they have different preferences and expectations. The tech blogosphere tends to rush to decide about things. I find they sometimes miss the mark, widely and I was sure this would be one of those times, which is why I didn't roll it out the usual way." created="Fri, 28 Dec 2007 17:28:02 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I wanted to get a base of users going, and learn and evolve the software, so far it looks pretty good, so the next step is to evaluate, listen, fix the most serious bugs I can find, think, and then move forward. " created="Fri, 28 Dec 2007 17:32:02 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Watch this space (below) for new features and fixes..." created="Fri, 28 Dec 2007 18:41:37 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Change Note #17: &lt;a href=&quot;http://codecasting.org/photoFan/00017.html&quot;&gt;List of newly-installed FlickrFans&lt;/a&gt;." created="Fri, 28 Dec 2007 21:26:41 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="End of year links" created="Fri, 28 Dec 2007 23:41:11 GMT">
					<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.nytimes.com/2007/12/23/weekinreview/23buzzwords.html?ex=1214370000&amp;en=93085a3e5ab92825&amp;ei=5087&amp;excamp=NYT-E-I-NYT-E-AT-1228-L24&amp;WT.mc_ev=click&amp;WT.mc_id=%20NYT-E-I-NYT-E-AT-1228-L24&quot;&gt;NY Times list&lt;/a&gt; of buzzwords of 2007." created="Sat, 29 Dec 2007 00:28:07 GMT"/>
